column1: Add support for Swift Package Manager
add ability to change drawer state to .closed by swipe to bottom
*Crashes* Make sure that feedback generator is being called on main thread
Support transparency for primary content container
Add an optional tap to toggle behavior
Change all of public properties and methods to open
Adding new feature to provide spacing around the drawer.
Support more corner positions, unified panelInsets, better safe area support.
Fix a bug where the drawer distance delegate method would initially be the incorrect distance
Specify default collapsed and partial reveal heights
Change xcconfig to pod_target_xcconfig in podspec
Added helper member for accessing PulleyViewController from any UIViewController
Split panelInset variable into left and top components.
Add missing Swift syntax highlighting in README
Fix issues with background dimming on iPhone X
Added support for TabBar in iOS10: It is now possible to add the Pull…
Mask the background dimming view behind the drawer so the drawer itself is not darkened
Amend drawerScrollView to respect safeAreInset in Landscape mode
Fixing podspec to work with new Xcode 9 build system
Add optional completion handlers for all animations that occur
Allow container view to be embedded in navVC
Added a Pulley framework to support Carthage
Updated view controller containment calls according to Apple’s Documentation
Dimming View tap recogniser not firing drawer position
Update for Xcode8b6 version of Swift 3.0
fixed the author in the podspec
